---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="What is Thumbrella?"
  description="Overview of Thumbrella and the developer-first information architecture for the site."
>
  <Section
    eyebrow="what is thumbrella"
    title="A product site shaped like a technical brief"
    lede="Thumbrella is presented as something to understand and inspect, not just something to be sold."
  >
    <p>
      The goal is to explain the media stack in the order a developer usually wants it: concept, capabilities, runnable browser example, client docs, then hosting details. That keeps the site aligned with evaluation work instead of generic funnel design.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Explain the product in plain technical language.</li>
      <li>Keep links to docs and runnable examples visible.</li>
      <li>Use a static-site architecture that stays easy to edit.</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>
</MainLayout>